The paper proposes a model for semi-supervised learning on graph-structured data, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model uses graph convolutional networks (GCNs), which is a specific technique within machine learning that has been applied to natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks. The paper also mentions the use of random walks, which is a common technique in network science and social network analysis (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.SI, cs.CL, and cs.CV.
